\f3\b\fs28 \cf0 Session One: Introduction to this course
\b0 \
\pard\tx1440\tx2160\fi720\sl288\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 In this course, you are assumed to understand that 
\b files
\b0  contain 
\b data
\b0 . 
\b Folders
\b0  are containers for collecting files and other folders into a related 
\b data set
\b0 . 
\b Mass storage
\b0  is a physical location for storing files and folders (data). Mass storage can be physically part of your computer, a device that plugs into your computer, or in "
\b the cloud
\b0 ". The cloud is simply a shorthand way of saying a remote storage location accessible by the internet.\
By the way, "data" is a plural noun. The singular is "datum". Write "data are"; but write "datum is".\
\
\pard\tx1440\tx2160\sl288\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\b \cf0 Considerations:\

\b0 How much do you care about organization? The simplest strategy for organizing your data is to put everything into a single folder (~Documents, for example) and hunt for it the stuff when you need it. I assume you have tried this and found it wanting. That's why you are in this course. While we are getting started, please consider how much effort you want to invest into a more complex strategy for organization. Nothing is free. If you want more organization, you need to invest time and perseverance into organization. Think about it.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\li720\fi-720\sl288\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9642 	}How much time are you willing to spend on organization?\
{\listtext	\uc0\u9642 	}Will you really use whatever strategy you choose?\
{\listtext	\uc0\u9642 	}Is the benefit worth the cost of creating and staying with a plan?\
